config BR2_DEBOOTSTRAP_HOST_DEBOOTSTRAP
	bool "host debootstrap"
	help
	  debootstrap is used to create a Debian base system
	  from scratch, without requiring the availability of
	  dpkg or apt. It does this by downloading .deb files
	  from a mirror site, and carefully unpacking them
	  into a directory which can eventually be chrooted
	  into.

	  https://salsa.debian.org/installer-team/debootstrap
